Setting up IntelliJ to run PHP and PHPUnit tests with XAMPP
---
1) Run the appropriate script (mac.sh, linux.sh, windows.bat) that will setup the sukrupa website
   on your locale machine and also pear and phpunit.
2) Open up the sukrupa-website intelliJ project file.
3) Go into your PHP settings (File > Settings > PHP for Windows/Linux, IntelliJ IDEA > Preferences for Mac). Change
   the PHP Home path to point to the /bin directory of your XAMPP installation, and click 'Update Include Paths'.
4) Run the test(s)!


Writing PHPUnit Tests
---
1) Add "require_once 'PHPUnit/Autoload.php';" to the top of the test file.
2) Either name ALL your test methods starting with 'test...' OR use
   this annotation /** @test */ above each test method.
   See www.phpunit.de/manual/current/en/writing-tests-for-phpunit.html


